{
  "text": "plantarum (MTCC 1325) were purchased from Microbial Type Culture Collection (MTCC) centre, Chandigarh, India. The strains were stored in Luria-Bertani (LB) medium containing 20 % glycerol at -20°C. LB Agar was used for routine culturing of the strains. Chlorpyrifos degradation analyses were carried out in Minimal Salt broth (MS broth). MS broth contained (g/L) Yeast Extract 1, K 2 HPO 4 1.5, KH 2 PO 4 0.5 g, (NH 4 ) 2 SO 4 0.5, NaCl 0.5, MgSO 4 0.2, CaCl 2 0.05, FeSO 4 0.02. 100 mg/L of chlorpyrifos was filter sterilized and used for degradation experiments [CITATION_1] ).",
